55-year-old Krugman is a Neokeynesian who teaches at Princeton University and is known for his regular articles for the New York Times.
Krugman is one of the biggest critics of the Bush administration's economic and foreign policy.
A few months after the September 11, 2001, attacks, during the days of the Enron collapse, Krugman claimed in a New York Times headline that this second event was more decisive in U.S. history than the attacks.
A prediction which received a great deal of controversy and which was presented to the economist years later, but which is now proven to be quite correct.
